LAGOS – Arik Air said it has increased frequencies on some of its major Northern routes to cope with customers’ demands. A statement by Mr. Adebanji Ola, the Spokesman of the airline, said that the airline is increasing daily frequencies on Abuja-Sokoto, Abuja-Kano, Abuja-Yola and Lagos-Jos routes. The statement hinted that the decision to add more frequencies to the scheduled flights on the aforementioned routes was informed by the need to give customers more choices on these destinations. Stanbic IBTC Set To Advance Customer Assets In 2022 Leky Mills Launches New Product Offering Similarly, he said the airline is making its tickets more affordable by introducing N23, 000 promotional fares across the network. The promotional fares, which became effective on Monday, January 17, 2020, Ola said are available in all modes of sales particularly on its website and airport/ city ticketing offices. Capt. Roy Ilegbodu, Arik Air’s Chief Executive Officer, said on the development: “We want to give our customers on the Sokoto, Kano, Yola and Jos routes more choices of flights to ease their travels. Also we want to further stimulate air travel among Nigerians by introducing promotional fares.”